how do you get over being home sick i am moving away from my family and at first i was really happy now i am becoming sad everyday what do i do about it thanks all for the advice i currently live in michigan and will be moving to florida on saturday i work with my dad so i am use to seeing him everyday so i think that i will miss him and my nephews the most but i really appreciate everyones advice thanks well everyone's different but here are a few things that i do when i start to miss someone i call them i push sad thoughts out of my mind and only let in the ones that make me laugh i kind of put my other life on hold and i just don't think much about it then when i go back to visit i un freeze it and carry on where i left off sometimes i also try to integrate the two lifestyles by having lots of pictures and things from home lying around if you have a pet bring hm her if i'm depressed i sing a happy song put on cheerful music or watch a funny movie make sure you have an active social life talk to your friends go home for regular visits if you can and when all else fails and even if it doesn't chocolate always helps keep smiling Friends The Catcher in the Rye Social rule Time Out of Mind The Ashlee Simpson Show Doug About a Boy Nico Robin Care Bears Rich Mullins The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Grandview, U.S.A. Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Negima Cliff Richard Blonde on Blonde Spidey Super Stories I Am Furious Yellow The Adventures of Pete & Pete Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Happiness W.I.T.C.H. The Smoking Room George Burns Goodness and value theory EastEnders Theory of conduct Knots Landing Insomnia Hall & Oates RuneScape quests Treehouse of Horror V Minstrel show Das Lied von der Erde Camp Lazlo Scenes from a Memory Laura Schlessinger Piccolo Junior Saga Phoebe Buffay's songs Sinfest Kurt Cobain Sheryl Crow Love and Theft Hey Jude Avenue Q Kodocha Carrie Jacobs-Bond Spot the Dog Year of the Spider Sly & the Family Stone Humphrey Bogart Milton H. Er